quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  96,1,"Recite in the name of your Lord Who created,",footnotes:182776:1|182777:2|182778:3
  96,2,"created man from a clot of congealed blood.",footnotes:182779:1
  96,3,"Recite: and your Lord is Most Generous,"
  96,4,"Who taught by the pen,",footnotes:182780:1
  96,5,"taught man what he did not know.",footnotes:182781:1
  96,6,"Nay, surely man transgresses;",footnotes:182782:1
  96,7,"for he believes himself to be self-sufficient.",footnotes:182783:1
  96,8,"Surely to your Lord is your return.",footnotes:182784:1
  96,9,"Did you see him who forbids"
  96,10,"a servant (of Allah) when he prays?",footnotes:182785:1
  96,11,"Did you consider: what if he is on the Right Way,"
  96,12,"and enjoins piety?"
  96,13,"Did you consider: what if he gives the lie (to the Truth) and turns away (from it)?"
  96,14,"Does he not know that Allah sees everything?",footnotes:182786:1
  96,15,"No indeed; if he does not desist, We shall drag him by the forelock;",footnotes:182787:1
  96,16,"by the lying forelock steeped in sin.",footnotes:182788:1
  96,17,"So let him summon his helpmates;",footnotes:182789:1
  96,18,"We too shall summon the guards of Hell.",footnotes:182790:1
  96,19,"No, not at all. Never obey him. But prostrate yourself and become nigh (to your Lord).",footnotes:182791:1
